 War.<br>FIFA again excluded.\n|-\n| 1921\n| {{dts|01|06|11|format=dm}}\n| SFA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Portpatrick]]}}\n| Portpatrick Hotel\n|\n|-\n| 1922\n| {{dts|01|06|10|format=dm}}\n| FAW\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|WAL|1807}} Llandudno}}\n| Imperial Hotel\n|\n|-\n| 1923\n| {{dts|01|06|09|format=dm}}\n| IFA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|NIR}} Giant's Causeway, Bushmills}}\n| Causeway Hotel\n| Last meeting to exclude FIFA\n|-\n| 1924\n| {{dts|01|06|14|format=dm}}\n| FA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|ENG}} London}}\n| Football Association Offices,<br>42 Russell Square\n| style=\"vertical-align: top;\" rowspan=27 | 2\n| style=\"vertical-align: top;\" rowspan=27 | 2\n| style=\"vertical-align: top;\" rowspan=27 | 2\n| style=\"vertical-align: top;\" rowspan=27 | 2\n| style=\"vertical-align: top;\" rowspan=27 | 2\n| style=\"vertical-align: top;\" rowspan=27 | 80%\n|\n|-\n| 1925\n| {{dts|01|06|13|format=dm}}\n| FIFA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|FRA}} Paris}}\n| 11 Rue de Londres\n|\n|-\n| 1926\n| {{dts|01|06|12|format=dm}}\n| SFA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|SCO}} [[St Andrews]]}}\n| Grand Hotel\n|\n|-\n| 1927\n| {{dts|01|06|11|format=dm}}\n| FAW\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|WAL|1807}} Llandudno}}\n| [[Grand Hotel (Llandudno)|Grand Hotel]]\n|\n|-\n| 1928\n| {{dts|01|06|09|format=dm}}\n| IFA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|NIR}} [[Newcastle, County Down|Newcastle]]}}\n| Slieve Donard Hotel\n|\n|-\n| 1929\n| {{dts|01|06|08|format=dm}}\n| FIFA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|FRA}} Paris}}\n| [[French Football Federation|F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Fran\u00e7aise de Football Association]] Offices,<br>22 Rue de Londres\n|\n|-\n| 1930\n| {{dts|01|06|14|format=dm}}\n| FA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Bournemouth]]}}\n| Royal Exeter Hotel\n|\n|-\n| 1931\n| {{dts|01|06|13|format=dm}}\n| SFA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Auchterarder]]}}\n| [[Gleneagles Hotel]]\n|\n|-\n| 1932\n| {{dts|01|06|11|format=dm}}\n| FAW\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|WAL|1807}} Llandudno}}\n| Imperial Hotel\n|\n|-\n| 1933\n| {{dts|01|06|10|format=dm}}\n| IFA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|NIR}} Portrush}}\n| Northern Counties Hotel\n| Rules amended to allow FIFA-hosted meetings to take place in \"the territory of a Continental National Association\", rather than being restricted to Paris.\n|-\n| 1934\n| {{dts|01|06|09|format=dm}}\n| FIFA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Cannes]]}}\n| [[:fr:H\u00f4tel_des_Anglais|H\u00f4tel des Anglais]]\n|\n|-\n| 1935\n| {{dts|01|06|08|format=dm}}\n| FA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Shanklin]]}}\n| Daish's Hotel\n|\n|-\n| 1936\n| {{dts|01|06|13|format=dm}}\n| SFA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Troon]]}}\n| Marine Hotel\n|\n|-\n| 1937\n| {{dts|01|06|12|format=dm}}\n| FAW\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|WAL|1807}} Llandudno}}\n| Imperial Hotel\n|\n|-\n| 1938\n| data-sort-value=\"000000000001-06-11-0000\" | 11 & 13 June\n| IFA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|NIR}} Portrush}}\n| Northern Counties Hotel\n|\n|-\n| 1939\n| {{dts|01|06|10|format=dm}}\n| FIFA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Nice]]}}\n| [[Hotel Negresco]]\n| Last meeting held before World War II. A meeting was scheduled for London in 1940, but was abandoned when FIFA and IFA delegates were unable to attend.\n|-\n| 1947\n| {{dts|01|06|14|format=dm}}\n| FA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|ENG}} Torquay}}\n| Imperial Hotel\n| First meeting held after World War II.\n|-\n| 1948\n| {{dts|01|06|12|format=dm}}\n| FIFA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|SUI}} [[Montreux]]}}\n| [[Fairmont Le Montreux Palace|Palace Hotel]]\n| First meeting held outside Britain, Ireland and France.<br>Meeting would have regularly been hosted by the SFA, but it was unanimously agreed to accept an invitation from FIFA to host this meeting.\n|-\n| 1949\n| {{dts|01|06|11|format=dm}}\n| SFA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Pitlochry]]}}\n| Hydro Hotel\n|\n|-\n| 1950\n| {{dts|01|06|10|format=dm}}\n| FAW\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|WAL|1807}} [[Beaumaris]]}}\n| Bulkeley Arms Hotel\n|\n|-\n| 1951\n| {{dts|01|06|09|format=dm}}\n| IFA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|NIR}} Portrush}}\n| Northern Counties Hotel\n|\n|-\n| 1952\n| {{dts|01|06