-\n| 1956\n| {{dts|01|06|16|format=dm}}\n| FAW\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|WAL|1953}} Llandudno}}\n| Imperial Hotel\n|\n|-\n| 1957\n| {{dts|01|06|15|format=dm}}\n| IFA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|NIR}} Portrush}}\n| Northern Counties Hotel\n|\n|-\n| 1958\n| {{dts|01|06|07|format=dm}}\n| FIFA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|SWE}} [[Stockholm]]}}\n| Hotel Foresta\n| style=\"vertical-align: top;\" rowspan=63 | 1\n| style=\"vertical-align: top;\" rowspan=63 | 1\n| style=\"vertical-align: top;\" rowspan=63 | 1\n| style=\"vertical-align: top;\" rowspan=63 | 1\n| style=\"vertical-align: top;\" rowspan=63 | 4\n| style=\"vertical-align: top;\" rowspan=63 | 75%\n| Meeting held on the day before the opening of the [[1958 FIFA World Cup|1958 World Cup]].<br>New rules adopted, with greater voting weight given to FIFA \"on behalf of all other National Associations in membership with it\".<br>Hosting rules changed to provide that \"when the FIFA Congress and the World Cup coincide\", FIFA should host the meeting at the World Cup venue, if practicable.<br>Date of meeting may be any time in June.\n|-\n| 1959\n| {{dts|01|06|20|format=dm}}\n| FA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|JEY|old}} [[Saint Helier|St. Helier, Jersey]]}}\n| Pomme d'Or Hotel <!-- https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/ca/Liberation_sculpture_Pomme_d%27Or_Jersey.jpg -->\n| First of four consecutive meetings hosted by the FA outside England in the [[Channel Islands]]\n|-\n| 1960\n| {{dts|01|06|18|format=dm}}\n| SFA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|SCO}} [[St Andrews]]}}\n| Rusack's Marine Hotel\n|\n|-\n| 1961\n| {{dts|01|06|17|format=dm}}\n| FAW\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|WAL}} [[Porthcawl]]}}\n| [[Seabank Hotel]]\n|\n|-\n| 1962\n| {{dts|01|06|23|format=dm}}\n| IFA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|NIR}} Newcastle}}\n| Slieve Donard Hotel\n|\n|-\n| 1963\n| {{dts|01|06|15|format=dm}}\n| FIFA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|ITA|1946}} [[Venice]]}}\n| Palazzo della Camera di Commercio\n|\n|-\n| 1964\n| {{dts|01|06|20|format=dm}}\n| FA\n| {{nowrap|{{flagicon|JEY|old}} St. 